    "This makes it difficult to pinpoint the source of improvements and limits the development of more effective or efficient alignment algorithms.",
    "In this work, we replicate modern alignment pipelines (Tunstall et al., 2023b; Xu et al., 2024b) and analyze sources in the training process that could affect performance.",
    "In the three-stage training of supervised fine-tuning (SFT), offline preference learning, and online preference learning, we find that: 1) sequence packing and loss masking significantly enhance SFT, 2) scaling offline preference datasets improves overall performance, and 3) online learning greatly benefits chat benchmarks.",
    "Then, we aggregate our findings and fine-tune from Gemma-2b-base (Gemma et al., 2024) and LLaMA-3-8b-base (AI@Meta, 2024) using publicly available datasets and open-source algorithms.",
    "We evaluate our models on popular benchmarks such as Arena-Hard (Zheng et al., 2023), AlpacaEval-2 (Li et al., 2023b), MT-Bench (Zheng et al., 2023), and OpenLLM (Beeching et al., 2023)."
